description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking to recruit a substantive Workforce Systems Lead. The Workforce Systems Lead will be required to &lt;/strong&gt;ensure that a high quality service is provided by the Workforce Systems team, which supports the achievement of both national and local key performance indicators (KPIs) through effective and efficient use of Workforce Systems. We are entering an &lt;strong&gt;exciting phase of development in transforming and optimising our existing services within our Workforce Department across Lancashire and South Cumbria NHS Foundation Trust. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate must have knowledge of ESR, e-rostering systems and registration authority. We are looking for an individual who is able to engage with key stakeholders and front-line staff so effective communication and people skills are essential. You will also provide line management support to the Workforce Systems team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be fully supported in the role to ensure you are able to develop your skills and capabilities. The ability to travel between trust sites and across the region is required for this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would love to hear from you and further discuss how you fit within our vision. For more information, please contact Andrew Hodgson on andrew.hodgson@lscft.nhs.uk or 07971337854&lt;/p&gt;
